
# Titanic - Machine Learning from Disaster

In this challenge, we build a predictive model that answers the question: ‚Äúwhat sorts of people were more likely to survive?‚Äù using passenger data (ie name, age, gender, socio-economic class, etc).




## Features

### Target Variable
- Survived : 0 = No, 1 = Yes

### Features
- Pclass: Passenger Class (1 = 1st, 2 = 2nd, 3 = 3rd)
- Sex: Male or Female
- Age: Age in years
- SibSp: Number of Siblings/Spouses Aboard
- Parch: Number of Parents/Children Aboard
- Fare: Passenger Fare
- Embarked_Q: Embarked at Queenstown (1 = Yes, 0 = No)
- Embarked_S: Embarked at Southampton (1 = Yes, 0 = No)
## Data source

* Source: Kaggle Titanic Dataset: https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/titanic/data
## Model Development

## Models Used

- Logistic Regression
- Decision Tree Classifier
- Random Forest Classifier
## Results
#### Accuracy:
- Logistic Regression: 80.68%
- Decision Tree Classifier: 82.95%
- Random Forest Classifier: 86.36%
